jerf started from two propositions, 
1) &quot;a sterotype exists&quot;
2) &quot;the study is correct&quot;
he argued that these propositions imply the proposition &quot;a stereotype does not exist.&quot; This contradicts the starting propositions. <i>If</i> you accept his argument then one of the starting propositions must be false. It could be the first, the second or both. He has not said which he believes to be true or false so your response is groundless.
